ason Logs\", description: \"Full context maps, document scores, and model reasoning thoughts are stored inside an IT ledger.\" },\n211 |           { score: 4, label: \"Deterministic Trace\", description: \"Every execution path is recorded on a secure ledger, with cryptographically signed action chains.\" }\n212 |         ]\n213 |       },\n214 |       {\n215 |         id: \"governance_q3\",\n216 |         text: \"What is your approach to AI bias, hallucinations, and red-teaming?\",\n217 |         options: [\n218 |           { score: 1, label: \"Reactive Fixes\", description: \"Errors or biased outputs are only investigated and patched after users or clients complain.\" },\n219 |           { score: 2, label: \"Manual Spot-Checking\", description: \"Operations teams manually review a small random percentage of transcripts once a month.\" },\n220 |           { score: 3, label: \"Continuous Eval Sets\", description: \"Automated regression tests run updated validation data against models prior to deployment.\" },\n221 |           { score: 4, label: \"Adversarial Stress\", description: \"Automated simulator models constantly attack system nodes to reveal security anomalies.\" }\n222 |         ]\n223 |       }\n224 |     ]\n225 |   },\n226 |   {\n227 |     id: \"techstack\",\n228 |     name: \"Technology & Infrastructure Stack\",\n229 |     shortName: \"Tech Stack\",\n230 |     color: \"#3B82F6\",\n231 |     borderColor: \"border-[#3B82F6]/20\",\n232 |     description: \"Sovereign compute layers, model serving architectures, and zero-latency legacy software integrations.\",\n233 |     questions: [\n234 |       {\n235 |         id: \"techstack_q1\",\n236 |         text: \"What represents your core machine learning model hosting setup?\",\n237 |         options: [\n238 |           { score: 1, label: \"Public API Subscriptions\", description: \"Direct HTTP connections to standard commercial vendors; no dedicated clusters or control.\" },\n239 |           { score: 2, label: \"Dedicated Cloud Enclaves\", description: \"Models deployed inside private corporate cloud tenants (VPCs) on standard hyperscaler infrastructure.\" },\n240 |           { score: 3, label: \"Sovereign Local Serving\", description: \"Highly optimized model hosting on dedicated physical enclaves or regional sandboxed clusters.\" },\n241 |           { score: 4, label: \"Dynamic Edge/Mesh Routing\", description: \"Decentralized mesh selecting nodes dynamically based on cost, performance, and localization laws.\" }\n242 |         ]\n243 |       },\n244 |       {\n245 |         id: \"techstack_q2\",\n246 |         text: \"How cleanly are your AI systems integrated with legacy systems (e.g. ERP, CRM)?\",\n247 |         options: [\n248 |           { score: 1, label: \"Manual Data Entry\", description: \"AI outputs text to a window; human employees manually re-type insights into target tools.\" },\n249 |           { score: 2, label: \"Batch File Overwrites\", description: \"Nightly cron operations copy spreadsheet files or database records to sync environments.\" },\n250 |           { score: 3, label: \"Active REST Connectors\", description: \"Structured microservices and authenticated API endpoints update systems in real-time.\" },\n251 |           { score: 4, label: \"Sovereign Event Streams\", description: \"Sovereign queues handle instant writebacks via transaction listeners with zero file persistence.\" }\n252 |         ]\n253 |       },\n254 |       {\n255 |         id: \"techstack_q3\",\n256 |         text: \"What is your architecture strategy for localized fine-tuning or training?\",\n257 |         options: [\n258 |           { score: 1, label: \"Zero Fine-Tuning\", description: \"Relying 100% on general base models out of the box with zero custom parameters.\" },\n259 |           { score: 2, label: \"Periodic Cloud Pipelines\", description: \"Cloud-based batch training runs executed every few months to adjust weights in cloud repositories.\" },\n260 |           { score: 3, label: \"Localized Parameter Tuning\", description: \"Dedicated on-site compute servers adjusting weight adapters (LoRAs) inside secured local servers.\" },\n261 |           { score: 4, label: \"Continuous Local Optimization\", description: \"Sovereign reinforcement loops continuously fine-tuning models on edge nodes securely.\" }\n262 |         ]\n263 |       }\n264 |     ]\n265 |   },\n266 |   {\n267 |     id: \"leadership\",\n268 |     name: \"Leadership & Commitment\",\n269 |     shortName: \"Leadership\",\n270 |     color: \"#E5A93C\",\n271 |     borderColor: \"border-[#E5A93C]/20\",\n272 |     description: \"C-suite engagement, executive sponsorship of long-term milestones, and willingness to absorb early friction.\",\n273 |     questions: [\n274 |       {\n275 |         id: \"leadership_q1\",\n276 |         text: \"To what level is the executive leadership team involved in your AI roadmap?\",\n277 |         options: [\n278 |           { score: 1, label: \"Passive Awareness\", description: \"C-suite is interested in news trends but treats AI as a secondary IT maintenance discussion.\" },\n279 |           { score: 2, label: \"Supportive Allocation\", description: \"Appoints budget limits for projects but leaves leadership direction and strategy to mid-level IT teams.\" },\n280 |           { score: 3, label: \"Active Sponsorship\", description: \"C-suite leaders champion efforts, reviewing telemetry and ROI scorecards on a monthly basis.\" },\n281 |           { score: 4, label: \"Visionary Direction\", description: \"AI is positioned as the central driver of business transformation in all executive and board plans.\" }\n282 |         ]\n283 |       },\n284 |       {\n285 |         id: \"leadership_q2\",\n286 |         text: \"How resilient is project funding to early organizational friction or delayed ROI?\",\n287 |         options: [\n288 |           { score: 1, label: \"Extremely Fragile\", description: \"Funding is threatened or cut if immediate quarterly ROI targets aren't successfully achieved.\" },\n289 |           { score: 2, label: \"Short-Term Rigid\", description: \"Capital is allocated annually, with rigid expectations that discourage creative risk-taking.\" },\n290 |           { score: 3, label: \"Protected Reserves\", description: \"Dedicated multi-year reserves designed to tolerate exploratory, non-linear development paths.\" },\n291 |           { score: 4, label: \"Sovereign Equity Model\", description: \"Continuous, milestone-linked funding that values data security and strategic capabilities as long-term assets.\" }\n292 |         ]\n293 |       },\n294 |       {\n295 |         id: \"leadership_q3\",\n296 |         text: \"What is leadership's risk tolerance regarding pioneering technology paradigms?\",\n297 |         options: [\n298 |           { score: 1, label: \"Highly Risk-Averse\", description: \"Wait until solutions are 100% standard and proven across competitors (years behind edge).\" },\n299 |           { score: 2, label: \"Conservative Follower\", description: \"Wait for initial enterprise case studies to emerge before initiating similar projects.\" },\n300 |           { score: 3, label: \"Calculated Early Adopter\", description: \"Willing to build custom enclaves or pilot novel agentic patterns to secure early strategic advantages.\" },\n301 |           { score: 4, label: \"Sovereign Pioneer\", description: \"Partnering with research centers, creating proprietary models, and carving custom technical paths.\" }\n302 |         ]\n303 |       }\n304 |     ]\n305 |   },\n306 |   {\n307 |     id: \"operating\",\n308 |     name: \"Operating Model & Delivery\",\n309 |     shortName: \"Operating Model\",\n310 |     color: \"#009DFF\",\n311 |     borderColor: \"border-[#009DFF]/20\",\n312 |     description: \"Co-working framework of human operators and cognitive agents, release velocities, and organizational structure.\",\n313 |     questions: [\n314 |       {\n315 |         id: \"operating_q1\",\n3