here, and what is *not* present: radar visuals, bar breakdowns, and maturity ladders are mentioned. It looks like it doesn't need fake benchmarks or guaranteed outcomes.\n\n\n**Defining the Display**\n\nI'm solidifying the design narrative. I visualize this assessment as a \"Telemetry Command Panel\" with a deep space obsidian aesthetic. I'll need a custom radar/web chart or maturity ladder to present the scores visually, combined with crisp borders and glow effects to achieve a high-quality presentation.\n\n\n**Formulating the Display**\n\nI'm now integrating new components into the `/build/assessment` display. I'm adding a \"GFF Pathway Matrix,\" visualized as interactive CSS/SVG cards to represent the GFF stages, highlighting the recommended path. I've also solidified a bento-style layout to present the information across several sections: a hero section with report details, a core scoring ring with maturity bands, and a custom interactive visual. I'm finalizing key diagnostic findings, recommended GFF pathways, dimension breakdowns, actionable roadmaps, and local utilities for managing the display.\n\n\n**Refining the Interactions**\n\nI'm now iterating on the interaction design. I'm focusing on animating the results with Framer Motion reveals, and I am adding hover micro-interactions to dimension breakdown cards and path cards. I'm also planning to incorporate a \"Telemetry Copied\" visual confirmation for copy-to-clipboard actions and a \"Save Diagnostic Archive\" download trigger. I'm considering tab transitions or highlights to represent maturity levels. I also want to address the mobile strategy: collapsing columns to full width, implementing touch-friendly action buttons, and considering horizontal scrolling or simplified layouts for charts on smaller viewports. I'm still deciding between components in `components/build/`, if there are any that may be relevant to use. I'll make sure to modify `/app/build/assessment/page.tsx` and, if necessary, `/app/build/assessment/data.ts` to keep changes contained.\n\n\n**Defining the Logic**\n\nI'm now making sure the assessment wizard is preserved as I enhance the results screen within `/app/build/assessment/page.tsx`. I'm starting to think about a helper function for calculating the GFF pathway, and how it will determine the recommended path based on the score. I've defined the paths based on score ranges: Garage (<35%), Foundry (35-59%), Factory (60-84%), and Operate (>=85%).\n\n\n"}}
